description: Experience the turnkey Residence 1814, a true 3 bedroom and 3 full bathroom, northeast corner residence at the Regatta tucked into the heart of Lakeshore East with unobstructed and permanent views of the Chicago River, Chicago's skyline and some of he most iconic and important buildings of the 1920s and 1930s Renaissance periods like the Merchandise Mart, Chicago Tribune Tower, Intercontinental Hotel an more modern structures of the last 25 years north of the river. Exquisite twilight and night time views north, west and east along the river and towards Lake Michigan and Navy Pier, Ohio Street Beach. Jut under 2000 square feet, Residence 1814 offers a formal entry, all hardwood floors throughout, open kitchen concept featuring chef's kitchen, 1.25" bullnosed granite counters, raised bar, KitchenAid stainless steel appliances, 42" all wood cabinetry with crown, glass panes, abundant storage space and drawers, open to living and separate dining areas, clear views to the lakeside. Floor to ceiling windows, balcony off living space. Staggered guest suite with ensuite bathroom off to the side, split apart from primary and second bedrooms. Custom lighting throughout from Lightology. Side by side washer and dryer. Sumptuous 22'x23' living and dining space combined. Each bathroom dressed in flor to ceiling natural marble stone. Primary bathroom with dual vanity, under mount sink, all wood vanity, separate shower and soaking tub, recessed medicine cabinets. Walk-in closet. Views from each room. This is a full amenity building with 24 hour doorstaff, onsite management, maintenance, engineer and property manager. Dry cleaners, library and common room, hospitality. Indoor lap pool, locker rooms, whirlpool, state of the art complete and comprehensive gym, beautifully outfitted hospitality room for private events, billiards room. Well funded with over $3.1M in reserves for 302 units. No special assessments. two side by side garage parking spaces (P4-263 and P4-264) included in the list price.
